org.knime.core.util.node.config

Class NodeConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.core.util.node.config.AbstractConfigElement
      • org.knime.core.util.node.config.NodeConfiguration

  • public class NodeConfiguration
extends AbstractConfigElement
    Represents a node configuration (parameters). In the simplest case it consists of a a list of simple configuration elements, such as string, int, double, etc., which are all identified by a unique identifier.
    Author:
    Bernd Wiswedel, KNIME.com, Zurich, Switzerland

    • Constructor Detail

      • NodeConfiguration

        public NodeConfiguration(ConfigRegistry registry)
        Creates a new configuration object from the configuration registry. The registry defines the fields that can be accessed using the various getters and setters for the supported types. Attempts to read fields that are undefined or have wrong types according to the registry will cause an InvalidSettingsException to be thrown.
        Parameters:
        registry - The registry with all valid fields.

      • getConfigElement

        protected <T extends AbstractConfigElement> T getConfigElement(String id,
                                                               Class<T> cl)
                                                        throws InvalidSettingsException
        Queries a config parameter that was registered during construction time.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the parameter
        Parameters:
        id - The ID under which the parameter is registered
        cl - The class to T.
        Returns:
        The config element, never null.
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - If the config parameter has not been registered or was registered under a different type.
        NullPointerException - If either argument is null.
